==English==
===Proper noun===
'''Ali Baba'''

# A [[fictional character]] featured in ''The Arabian Nights'', famous for his encounter with forty [[thieves]].
# {{slang}} An extremely [[lucky]] person, especially one who aquires a large fortune by luck or by chance. Example: "My boss has a fortune hidden in a bank account in Greece, which he aquired through illicit deals - he is a real Ali Baba."